
                   <p style="text-align: center">
                       <b>Title:</b> You can’t perform certain maintenance procedures at the same time you are running the EC rebalance
procedure.<br>
                       <b>Bounding box:</b> x1=134, y1=698, x2=1566, y2=2061
                   </p>
                   <div align="center"><table border="1" class="dataframe">
  <thead>
    <tr style="text-align: right;">
      <th></th>
      <th>0</th>
      <th>1</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th>0</th>
      <td>Procedure</td>
      <td>Allowed during EC rebalance procedure?</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>1</th>
      <td>Additional EC rebalance\nprocedures</td>
      <td>No.\nYou can only run one EC rebalance procedure at a time.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>2</th>
      <td>Decommission procedure\nEC data repair job</td>
      <td>No.\n• You are prevented from starting a decommission procedure or an\nEC data repair while the EC rebalance procedure is running.\n• You are prevented from starting the EC rebalance procedure while a\nStorage Node decommission procedure or an EC data repair is\nrunning.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>3</th>
      <td>Expansion procedure</td>
      <td>No.\nIf you need to add new Storage Nodes in an expansion, run the EC\nrebalance procedure after adding all new nodes.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>4</th>
      <td>Upgrade procedure</td>
      <td>No.\nIf you need to upgrade StorageGRID software, perform the upgrade\nprocedure before or after running the EC rebalance procedure. As\nrequired, you can terminate the EC rebalance procedure to perform a\nsoftware upgrade.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>5</th>
      <td>Appliance node clone procedure</td>
      <td>No.\nIf you need to clone an appliance Storage Node, run the EC rebalance\nprocedure after adding the new node.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>6</th>
      <td>Hotfix procedure</td>
      <td>Yes.\nYou can apply a StorageGRID hotfix while the EC rebalance procedure\nis running.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table></div>
